#: classes/Admin/tpl/settings.php:30
msgid ""
"Saves voting data in the database. This enables the re-voting mechanism and "
"prevents logged-in users from voting multiple times, or non-logged-in users "
"from voting multiple times from the same IP address. If this option is "
"disabled, voting is checked by cookies only."
msgstr ""

#: classes/Admin/tpl/settings.php:31
msgid ""
"INFO: If a user is logged in, their vote is checked by their WP account. If "
"a user is not logged in, their IP address is checked. The downside of IP "
"checks is that a site may be visited from an enterprise network with a "
"shared IP address, so all users from that network are allowed to vote only "
"once."
msgstr ""

